What we shipped (v5):

tools/track_subject.py — three-stage smoothing pipeline replacing the old single EMA pass:

1. Linear interpolation (replaces forward-fill): gaps between sampled detections are now ramped smoothly instead of snapping to the new position all at once.
2. Median filter (_median_filter(), kernel=7): removes single-frame outlier detections (e.g. body/face mode switches) before smoothing. One bad frame can't swing the window.
3. Gaussian smoothing (_smooth(), sigma=3.0): replaces EMA. Acausal (looks forward and back), no lag artifact. Falls back to EMA if scipy isn't installed.

New optional params on write_tracked_vertical() and detect_crop_trajectory(): sigma=3.0, median_kernel=7. Existing callers unchanged.

Where to pick up next: sigma (3.0) and median_kernel (7) are hardcoded defaults — a CLI flag (--sigma, --kernel) per clip would let you tune per-shot without touching code. Per-clip subject hints in the CSV were also previously discussed and still unbuilt.



